1
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:13,823
Alla känner av oss själva.

2
00:00:14,624 --> 00:00:19,205
Och så i självförsörjning skrattar vi och tittar på människan tolerant som objekt av amusering.

3
00:00:20,225 --> 00:00:23,167
Men deras liknande till människor är mycket mer än skinn i djupet.

4
00:00:23,306 --> 00:00:24,367
Och från deras historia...

5
00:00:27,065 --> 00:00:29,725
In the wild, monkeys are creatures of strength and grace.

6
00:00:29,745 --> 00:00:35,968
Through living in the trees, the first monkeys grew serviceable hands to help them in their journeys through the branches.

7
00:00:36,048 --> 00:00:42,909
Some, in the forests of the new world, strengthened their tails until they became a fifth limb, strong enough to support the whole weight of their bodies.

8
00:00:45,051 --> 00:00:49,332
As the year went on, they had to reckon with more enemies and different problems from those of the treetops.

9
00:00:50,192 --> 00:00:56,334
For defense and attack, they came to rely more and more on their hands and on the well-developed brains which life in the trees had given them.

10
00:00:58,203 --> 00:01:01,904
Baboons are fond of each others company and live together in large packs.

11
00:01:02,804 --> 00:01:10,628
They love the sunshine and on a fine day the whole colony... They are not hunting for fleas but for loose pieces of skin, thorns and so on.

12
00:01:10,828 --> 00:01:12,128
And they also pull out hairs.

13
00:01:13,248 --> 00:01:17,549
It stimulates the nerves of their skin and they obviously get a great deal of pleasure from it.

14
00:01:17,569 --> 00:01:20,611
Just as a man does from massage or a woman from beauty treatment.

15
00:01:20,632 --> 00:01:23,433
This urge to groom is tremendous.

16
00:01:23,472 --> 00:01:26,754
In their packs baboons have a definite social order arranged like our own.

17
00:01:27,631 --> 00:01:32,472
Each colony is made up of a number of families, and each family is under the leadership of an adult male.

18
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:36,515
He has one or more females attached to him, and probably several children.

19
00:01:37,555 --> 00:01:44,597
These families, which may remain together year after year, are the basic units of all monkey society.

20
00:01:44,638 --> 00:01:51,200
Early they are young under their bellies, and the young baboon can use its hands as soon as it's born to cling tightly to its mother's fur.

21
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,382
Apart from this, it's quite helpless.

22
00:01:54,421 --> 00:01:56,563
Young monkeys are usually born only one at a time.

23
00:01:57,435 --> 00:02:04,078
Från 5 och 6 års ålder stannar de med deras familjer och deras föräldrar och äldre barn är alltid tillgängliga för att skydda och hjälpa.

24
00:02:04,998 --> 00:02:08,561
Den här långa perioden av växten ger de unga djurna mycket tid för att lära sig.

25
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:16,004
De har muskler och limmor och försöker att göra de olika aktiviteterna av de äldre som är runt dem.

26
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:21,187
Dina föräldrar kommer att skada.

27
00:02:22,843 --> 00:02:28,324
Baboons have pouches in their cheeks into which they stuff the food until a convenient opportunity occurs to eat it.

28
00:02:32,787 --> 00:02:35,747
The overlord guards jealously the unity of his family.

29
00:02:36,568 --> 00:02:37,207
He is females.

30
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:11,445
Högre i skålen kommer de antropologiska aporna.

31
00:03:11,506 --> 00:03:15,188
De har inga händer och har större hjärnor än människan.

32
00:03:15,229 --> 00:03:18,671
Av de människa kreaturerna, de enda som lever helt i trädet är gibbonarna.

33
00:03:20,145 --> 00:03:22,705
Det är det mest gräsfulla av alla djur.

34
00:03:22,725 --> 00:03:28,146
Gay och livlig, vackert agil, de använder sina långa armar för att svänga genom bränslen med fantastisk frihet.

35
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:38,189
På deras röda avstånd till grunden, de går i rakt, och är de enda mammorna utan män som vanligtvis går på två fötter.

36
00:04:20,168 --> 00:04:28,014
In the early morning, the jungles of Malay and southern China are said to ring with the shrill chorus of the gibbons as they leave their sheltered sleeping places.

37
00:04:46,192 --> 00:04:50,194
Begin to approach human standards in the larger man like apes such as the orangutan.

38
00:04:51,115 --> 00:04:55,377
So human are these great apes that at one time they were thought to be a race of savage people.

39
00:04:56,177 --> 00:04:58,418
The name orangutan means wild man of the woods.

40
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:05,482
As night approaches the apes build nests in the trees to sleep in.

41
00:05:06,122 --> 00:05:07,744
These nests are not permanent homes.

42
00:05:07,764 --> 00:05:12,326
They are only slept in once and next morning the family moves on to new feeding grounds.

43
00:05:15,754 --> 00:05:16,434
Lively as light.

44
00:05:19,216 --> 00:05:22,958
They live in the same family groups as the monkeys, but their packs are much smaller.

45
00:05:23,718 --> 00:05:26,040
Each family is dominated by an adult male.

46
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:45,129
In captivity, the human being replaces the dominant male, and the normal impulses of the animals can be suppressed so long as the keeper is at hand.

47
00:05:45,608 --> 00:05:51,533
Och de kan lära sig att behålla sig som män och kvinnor, mer eller mindre.

48
00:05:51,553 --> 00:05:54,656
Deras diet, som alla mönster och apor, är nästan helt vegetariska.

49
00:06:06,127 --> 00:06:08,389
Men en människa har en rätt stor del av maten.

50
00:06:08,428 --> 00:06:12,232
Men det finns ingen anledning till att om hållaren var tillbaka, den stora människan hade mest av det.

51
00:06:29,855 --> 00:06:33,476
The apes, like the monkeys, take a tremendous interest in the fur of other animals.

52
00:06:34,257 --> 00:06:38,519
This instinct shows itself in captivity in a passion for investigating articles of clothing.

53
00:06:39,341 --> 00:06:41,141
Shoes particularly attract some apes.

54
00:06:41,903 --> 00:06:47,605
In taking off a man's shoe, the chimpanzee shows a command of hand and eye far beyond the ability of a young human child.

55
00:06:48,326 --> 00:06:50,648
But it hasn't the constructive intelligence to put it on again.

56
00:06:57,891 --> 00:07:01,913
Det är en attraktiv del av maten, säg en kupp icecream, som är avgörande av armarna.

57
00:07:02,293 --> 00:07:04,795
Den använder en stick för att få till det, för att skapa en lösning.

58
00:07:04,855 --> 00:07:07,076
Och de har varit kända för att sätta två ihop för en anledning.

59
00:07:07,096 --> 00:07:15,281
De ser ut att lösa ett problem som det här, inte bara av trial and error, som en katt eller en kvinna, men också av att studera situationen som en människa.

60
00:07:41,911 --> 00:07:44,213
Oavsett om apen har en definitiv känsla för ljud och rytm.

61
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:49,158
I råd eller utrymme kommer de att slå rytmiskt med händerna och fötterna på vilken som helst surface.

62
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,579
Det här känslan för rytm blir en primitiv dans.

63
00:08:10,338 --> 00:08:15,161
Samma här lär sig secret av Mankins passion för dansning och dansmusik.

64
00:09:10,289 --> 00:09:17,197
Det är fortfarande större, mer skrämmande människa kreaturer som glömmer sig i skärmen av skogen och flyr från interkurs med män.

65
00:09:18,136 --> 00:09:23,059
Like the other apes, but in all proportion like a man, but are more like giants in stature.

66
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:27,282
They cannot speak and have no understanding more than a beast.

67
00:09:27,322 --> 00:09:37,067
Many times they fall upon the elephants, which come to feed where they be, and so beat them with their clubbed fists and pieces of wood, that the elephants will run roaring away from them.

68
00:09:38,606 --> 00:09:46,772
At some time, such creature as this developed speech and became man.

69
00:09:46,792 --> 00:09:47,331
Man could speak.

70
00:09:48,153 --> 00:09:49,695
He could communicate with his fellows.

71
00:09:50,195 --> 00:09:52,655
He left the forests and lived in the open.

72
00:09:52,676 --> 00:09:54,275
He changed his habits of feeding.

73
00:09:55,197 --> 00:09:58,317
Unlike the apes he no longer accepted his world as he found it.

74
00:09:58,378 --> 00:10:02,999
With his brain and hands and tongue he shaped it to please himself.

75
00:10:04,299 --> 00:10:06,541
He imposed his own ways of life on his world.

76
00:10:06,561 --> 00:10:08,301
Built his own surroundings.

77
00:10:08,321 --> 00:10:11,121
Created a multitude of machines to do his will.

78
00:10:12,462 --> 00:10:14,923
He harnessed the elements for transport and communication.

79
00:10:15,796 --> 00:10:16,916
The physical world became his servant.

80
00:10:16,936 --> 00:10:21,298
But in all the complexity of a man-made world the family remains the root of society just as it was amongst the apes and the monkeys.

81
00:10:21,337 --> 00:10:24,019
In our families we spend the impressionable years of childhood.

82
00:10:24,038 --> 00:10:26,139
In our family circle we learn the behavior of civilized life.

83
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:27,799
We learn to keep our bodies well and fit with healthy exercise.

84
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:30,642
We learn how important it is to take pride in our outward appearance.

85
00:10:46,327 --> 00:10:53,035
Ifall vi har konstant exempel på våra föräldrar, kan det vara en förändring i samhället.

86
00:10:53,076 --> 00:10:54,778
En familj är den högsta uppgiften i livet.
